# React Patterns

## Components
- Use functional components only
- Extract custom hooks for reusable state/logic
- Colocate component-specific styles with the component

## Client vs Server
- Default to Server Components (no `"use client"`)
- Add `"use client"` at the top of the file only when using: hooks, event handlers, browser APIs, or context

## State & Props
- Prefer composition over prop drilling
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props with explicit children when needed

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - typed props
interface RecipeCardProps {
  title: string;
  description: string;
  slug: string;
}

export function RecipeCard({ title, description, slug }: RecipeCardProps) {
  return (/* ... */);
}
```
